-- Apax Wants $700 Million for Thomas Tank Engine, Telegraph Says
-- B y   J a c k   J o r d a n
-- 2010-10-09T10:45:13Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-09/apax-wants-700-million-for-thomas-tank-engine-telegraph-says.html
Apax Partners LLP wants $700 million
for Thomas the Tank Engine, an asset of  HIT Entertainment Ltd .,
the Telegraph reported, citing unidentified people.  Apax, the private-equity owner of HIT, has been approached
by Mr. Men owner  Chorion Plc  over the deal, the newspaper
reported. Other interested parties include Viacom Inc. and The
Walt Disney Co., the Telegraph said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Jack Jordan  in London at 
 jjordan22@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Mike Harrison at 
